    "Id": "chassisdef_ziegfried_ZF-D19",
    "Name": "Ziegfried",
    "Details": "The Ziegfried ZF-D19 is a 65-ton Kallon Industries heavy BattleMech introduced in 3054 for the Armed Forces of the Federated Commonwealth, designed around a right-arm Sword and chassis-wide Triple Strength Myomer that substantially amplifies melee damage and movement when heat reaches activation threshold. An all-energy weapons suite of an ER PPC, three Medium Pulse Lasers distributed across the torsos, and a center-torso ER Small Laser serves dual purpose, providing genuine ranged threat while deliberately building heat to keep the TSM engaged during close-quarters combat.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Melee Actuators</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.09</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limit: Left Lower</color>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_ziegfried"
